         <abstract>
            <p>The modulus and phase of the reduced logarithmic derivative of the cylindrical Bessel function $$zJ'_\nu(z)/J_\nu(z),$$ for complex variable $z$ and real order $\nu$, are investigated. Special attention is paid to the location of saddle points and their trajectories as $\nu$ varies.</p>
